Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Guaranty Trust Bank; FCMB of Nigeria

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-07-22T16:39:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-guaranty-trust-bank-fcmb-of-nigeria.html
Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index snapped
four days of declines, strengthening 0.2 percent to 2,048.19 by
the 1:30 p.m. close in  Port Louis .  The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index climbed for a
third day, increasing 0.6 percent to 23,925.72 by the 2:30 p.m.
close in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from the
bourse. Kenya’s All-Share Index fell for a third day, weakening
less than 0.1 percent to 67.08 by the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi,
the lowest since March 2010. The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite
Index retreated 0.4 percent to 1,178 by the 3 p.m. close in
Accra. Namibia’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  declined 0.1 percent
to 847.95 by the 4 p.m. close in Windhoek.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  First City Monument Bank Plc (FCMB)  ,  Nigeria ’s seventh
biggest lender by market value, rose 11 kobo, or 1.9 percent, to
6.06 naira, after the Lagos-based company said net income jumped
to 5.3 billion naira ($34.7 million) in the six months through
June, from 2.8 billion naira a year earlier.  Guaranty Trust Assurance Plc (GTASSURE)  , a Nigerian
insurer, gained 4 kobo, or 2.8 percent, to 1.47 naira, after
 Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY)  , said it would sell its
stake in the Lagos-based company for 11.9 billion naira to Assur
Africa Holding. Guaranty Trust Bank advanced 69 kobo, or 4.9
percent, to 14.79 naira, the biggest closing gain since March
22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
